Yes, I know. 💀 I’m just saying.. well young Lucy meets him and he accepts her just how she is and she falls in love, but she has this voice in her head telling her all the worst possible paranoid assumptions about it all and it makes her hurt people, including Kouta.. and when she sees him with his cousin she loses it and ends up killing his family. And at first she doesn’t really even realize how what she did wrong. She just wanted to love him she thinks and is sad that it ended up like that. Not understanding that it’s her own actions that got her to this point. But finally when she escapes the lab and meets Kouta again it begins her arc of redemption and atonement… she wants to change and become a “nyu” person.. and by the end she finally understands the concept of unselfish love. That’s why this is the only part that made me cry, at the end
